article.headline: Giffa has 29 in High Point's 86-79 win against Charleston Southern
article.description: — Kezza Giffa had 29 points in High Point's 86-79 win over Charleston Southern on Saturday night.
article.linkText: Giffa has 29 in High Point's 86-79 win against Charleston Southern
article.story: HIGH POINT, N.C. -- — Kezza Giffa had 29 points in High Point's 86-79 win over Charleston Southern on Saturday night. Giffa also added five assists for the Panthers (16-4, 5-0 Big South Conference). Kimani Hamilton added 26 points while going 9 of 20 from the floor, including 3 for 8 from 3-point range, and 5 for 8 from the foul line, and grabbed nine rebounds. Abdoulaye was 5-of-8 shooting, including 2 for 3 from 3-point range, and went 4 for 4 from the free-throw line to finish with 16 points. The Panthers picked up their eighth straight win. Taje' Kelly led the way for the Buccaneers (6-12, 2-3) with 25 points and eight rebounds. Charleston Southern also got 25 points and four assists from RJ Johnson. In addition, A'lahn Sumler finished with 14 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
